    <!-- Tutorial -->
    <string name="tutorial">Tutorial</string>
    <string name="tutorial_header">First steps</string>
    <string name="tutorial_page1">
        Attention: To call this tutorial later, go to help in the upper right corner of the menu!

        Welcome to Necromancy!\n\n

        This game is location based and works with GPS, which means where you standing right now,
        also your character is standing. To move, go outside and explore your surroundings.\n
        you can see which places near you, on the overview map at lower right corner of the game screen.\n\n

        At first, you probably will not know what to do.
        To help you get started we going to explain how to build your warehouse and gather the first raw materials,
        then you should master the basics to keep growing.\n\n
    </string>
    <string name="tutorial_page2_1">
        As a little welcome gift, you get your first corpse from us, it\'s in your inventory.
        Corpses can be resurrected into zombies, to do this, you have to select your spellbook at the character menu at left, chose the appropriate page and press summon.
        You\'ll need mana and the corpse to do this. Every three minutes you recharge your mana depending on your mana regeneration. If your zombie dies, you can repeal the corpse from ground.\n\n

        Humanoid corpses and bones can be found in cemeteries and hospitals,
        If you need more you should make a detour there.
    </string>
    <string name="tutorial_page3_1">If you have your first corpses, we should build a warehouse. Since you will often access it, it is best to put it in a place where you often spend your time, preferably your home. To start building, place yourself where the warehouse is to be built, go to the tree menu and select the warehouse.\n\nNow the unfinished warehouse should appear on the map. To build it now you need your undead. Summon a zombie or skeleton, select "Use" in the units menu, and execute the command on the site, then your unit should start moving and start building your warehouse.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_page4_1">When your warehouse is finished, we can collect resources for further projects. Now that your unit is out of action, we send it out to collect wood, stones or metals. Go back to the menu of your unit, choose "Use", switch to your overview map (Note: You can see and command your units in the default view and on the overview map.) and send your unit to a forest, a mine or a quarry. If all goes well, your undead will start to get raw materials for you. Depending on the distance and speed of the unit that takes a bit. When your unit is back, you can pick up the raw materials you brought from your warehouse.\n\nIf you have collected enough resources then you should build your fortress next. \n\nIf you have further questions, you can post them in our forum.\n\nWe wish you success!</string>
